messages.content:
THOUGHT: The dominance violation stems from newly created shuffle instructions being inserted after their uses for gather nodes. A safe, targeted fix is to adjust the insertion point only for gather entries: insert before the main operation (handling PHIs) for gathers to ensure dominance, while keeping the original behavior for non-gathers to avoid widespread test disruptions. I will modify setInsertPointAfterBundle to use FrontIt for E->isGather(), and retain LastInstIt/next-non-debug insertion for others.

```bash
sed -i '13714,13733c\void BoUpSLP::setInsertPointAfterBundle(const TreeEntry *E) {
  auto *Front = E->getMainOp();
  Instruction *LastInst = &getLastInstructionInBundle(E);
  assert(LastInst && "Failed to find last instruction in bundle");
  BasicBlock::iterator LastInstIt = LastInst->getIterator();
  bool IsPHI = isa<PHINode>(LastInst);
  if (IsPHI)
    LastInstIt = LastInst->getParent()->getFirstNonPHIIt();
  // For gather nodes, insert before the main op to ensure dominance of newly created defs.
  if (E->isGather()) {
    BasicBlock::iterator FrontIt = Front->getIterator();
    if (isa<PHINode>(Front))
      FrontIt = Front->getParent()->getFirstNonPHIIt();
    Builder.SetInsertPoint(Front->getParent(), FrontIt);
  } else if (IsPHI || (!E->isGather() && doesNotNeedToSchedule(E->Scalars))) {
    Builder.SetInsertPoint(LastInst->getParent(), LastInstIt);
  } else {
    // Original behavior: insert after the last instruction in the bundle for non-gathers.
    Builder.SetInsertPoint(
        LastInst->getParent(),
        LastInst->getNextNonDebugInstruction()->getIterator());
  }
  Builder.SetCurrentDebugLocation(Front->getDebugLoc());
}
' llvm/lib/Transforms/Vectorize/SLPVectorizer.cpp
```

